Two quick-fire second-half goals saw Swindon Town earn a draw against Hartlepool United.Pools took an early two-goal lead, Adam Boyd tapping home from eight yards and Antony Sweeney pouncing on Lescinel Jean-Francois' poor headed backpass. The Robins pulled one back through substitute Thomas Dossevi, who lashed a first-time strike past Scott Flinders. Two minutes later, striker Charlie Austin levelled, finding the net after a Hartlepool defensive mix-up. Swindon manager Danny Wilson told BBC Wiltshire: "Giving the two goals away that we gave away were absolutely abysmal and that's cost us.
Please turn on JavaScript. Media requires JavaScript to play. "To comeback against any team is always difficult but we always felt if we got a first goal we've got a chance. "We persevered, we had some good chances and we could have possibly won it at the end." Live text and stats
